            "description": "The Subsea Well Response Project (SWRP) is a non-profit joint initiative of nine major oil and\ngas companies, established on the recommendation of the International Association of Oil and\nGas Producers (OGP), aiming at developing solutions to respond quickly and efficiently to future\nsubsea well-control incidents.\nSWRP has assigned, through Oil Spill Response Ltd (OSRL) a contract to Saipem, Carubi and INNOVO for the engineering, procurement, fabrication and testing of the Offset Installation Equipment (OIE), a tool designed to install a capping stack on a blowout well without requiring direct vertical access.\nThis will allow supporting vessels to stay outside the zone in which it is unsafe to operate, i.e. the\nExclusion Zone.\nThe OIE utilizes a large subsea buoyant carrier structure to install the pre-designed capping\nstack over the blowout well.\n\nCLIENT: SAIPEM for PROJECT JOINT VENTURE AND CONSORTIUM SUBSEA WELL; OIL SPILL RE-SPONSE; SHELL; BP; CHEVRON; CONOCOPHILLIPS; EXXON; PETROBRAS; STATOIL; TOTAL.\n\nCONTRACTOR: CARTUBI and INNOVO.\nLOCATION: TRIESTE, ITALY - CARTUBI SHIPYARD\n\nMAIN ACTIVITIES:\n\n- Piping and flexible hoses (design and engineering, 3D model management, procurement, \nfabrication and installation supervision, modifications on the field)\n- Piping and flexible hoses testing procedures (pressure and flushing tests)\n- Carter for rigid piping (design and engineering, procurement, fabbrication and installation\nsupervision)\n- Lifting procedure of assemblies and sub-assemblies (lifting analyses, calculation notes and field\nsupervision)\n- Lifting Tools (design and engineering, procurement and fabbrication supervision)\n",
