            "description": "Master Thesis in Naval Architect and Marine Engineering:\n\nThe objective of this thesis was the analysis and modification of the rudder installed on the ship\nBithia owned by Tirrenia Compagnia Italiana di Navigazione and built by Fincantieri - Cantieri\nNavali SpA.\n\nIt was a team work by four colleagues and we edited the parts of:\n\n\u2022 Hydrodynamic analysis and geometry definition;\n\u2022 Structural design\n\u2022 Finite Element Analysis;\n\u2022 Construction and detailing design.\n\nI personally was in charge of the hydrodynamics, writing a Fortran program that allows the\nrudders design taking into account the propeller, hull and rudder interaction, and the resulting\nstream.\n\nThe whole project was focused on reducing the design time, using a single model created with\nthe software SmartMarine3D which is interfaced with all the design phases.\n",
